{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2016}} {{Infobox dot-com company |name = Beelinguapp |logo = Beelinguapp.png |author = [[David Montiel]] |type = Language Learning |url = {{URL|https://www.beelinguapp.com}} |language = {{Collapsible list |title=Multilingual |English |French |Spanish |German |Portuguese |Russian |Turkish |Arabic |Japanese |Korean |Italian |Chinese <small>(Mandarin)</small> |Hindi }} |launch_date = {{start date and age|2016|9|1|df=yes}}
}} [[File:Beelinguapp screenshot.png|thumb|a screenshot of beelinguapp showing a text in both English and Spanish|thumb|A screenshot of Beelinguapp showing English and Spanish simultaneously]] '''Beelinguapp''' is a [[language education|language-learning]] mobile application. It works by showing a text to the user in two languages simultaneously, allowing the users to use their native language as a reference. It works also as an audio book, users listen to a recording of a voice reading a text while at the same time a karaoke style animation moves through the text in both languages.The app offers different kinds of texts across 12 languages; with additional languages in development. Beelinguapp app is available on Android<ref name=googleplay>{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.david.android.languageswitch |title=Beelinguapp: Learn Languages |publisher=Google Play |date=October 11, 2016|accessdate=October 11, 2016}}</ref> and iOS.<ref name=appstore>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/app/beelinguapp-learn-languages-with-audio-books/id1225056371 |title=Beelinguapp: Learn Languages with Audiobooks |publisher=Apple App Store|date=September 11, 2017|accessdate=September 11, 2017}}</ref>
==Learning method== Beelinguapp works under two concepts it calls "Side by Side Reading" and "Karaoke Reading". The "Side by Side Reading" shows the user a text in a split screen in two languages side by side, the idea being that the user reads a text in the language being practiced but can always use their native language as a reference. "Karaoke Reading" means that the audio will be playing while the user is reading and a karaoke-style animation will be shown in both the learning and reference languages.
==History== Beelinguapp's creator, David Montiel, born in Mexico and located in Berlin, Germany, had been having difficulties reading texts and listening to audio books in German. When confronted by a word he still did not know, he realized it was too much of a problem to look for it in the dictionary and figure out which of the definitions suited better in the text. This is how the idea of a text in two languages simultaneously was born. One year after its conception, in September 2016, Beelinguapp went live.
==Initial financing and early recognition== In December 2016, Beelinguapp opened a Kickstarter campaign<ref name=kickstarter>{{cite web|url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/340177192/beelinguapp-read-and-listen-two-languages-in-paral/ |title=Beelinguapp: Learn any Language! |publisher=Kickstarter |date=December 12, 2016|accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref> to receive financing for the development of the iOS version of the app and the translation of more stories. By January 2017 the campaign was successful and the development of the iOS version started. In February, 2017 it was featured in the Huffington Post as one of the best 10 Kickstarter project of 2016.<ref name=huffpost>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/10-kickstarter-projects-that-make-2017-better-than_us_589b586ce4b0985224db5cc0 |title=10 Kickstarter Projects That Make 2017 Better Than 2016|publisher=Huffington Post |date=February 5, 2017|accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref> Beelinguapp has been featured in Google Play's "Editor's Choice" section, where they recommended 5 language learning apps in the market from around the world <ref name=talkthetalk>{{cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/topic?id=editorial_language_learning_apps_us |title=Talk the Talk With These 5 Language Learning Apps|publisher=Google Play |date=May 1, 2017|accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref> and has been named in news articles and blog posts among the best tools to learn Spanish<ref name=spanish>{{cite web|url=http://thedroidguy.com/2017/05/5-best-android-apps-learn-spanish-2017-1072786 |title=5 Best Android Apps to Learn Spanish in 2017|publisher=thedroidguy |date=May 23, 2017|accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref> and German.<ref name=german>{{cite web|url=http://theheureka.com/language-learning-apps-a-roundup-of-the-best-tools-to-learn-german-20170405 |title=Language learning apps: The best tools to master German |publisher=The Heureka |date=April 5, 2017|accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref> In May, 2017, Beelinguapp was certified by [[Mike Sharples]] and the Educational App Store and added to the Educational App Store Catalog.<ref name=edcational>{{cite web|url=https://www.educationalappstore.com/app/beelinguapp-learn-languages |title=Beelinguapp: Learn Languages |date=May 15, 2017|accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref> On June 6, 2017, The Mexican newspaper [[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]] wrote a featured article about Beelinguapp in both the online site and its printed version.<ref name=eluniversal>{{cite web|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/entrada-de-opinion/colaboracion/orgullomexicano/periodismo-de-investigacion/2017/06/3/app-mexicana |title=App Mexicana triunfa en Alemania |date=June 3, 2017|accessdate=June 3, 2017}}</ref> On June, 2017 it was selected by [[Google Play]] as an "Editor's Choice" app.
==Business model== Beelinguapp has several texts of different kinds, such as fairy tales, science texts, excerpts from novels, short stories, popular stories, and every week more texts are added. Some of these texts can be unlocked by in-app purchases or by subscribing to the service.
