{{unreferenced|date=October 2009}} {{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Madhukar Keche | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = मधुकर केचे | native_name_lang = Devanagari | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1932 | birth_place = Maharashtra, India | death_date = 1993 | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = | language = | nationality = Indian | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = Rashtrasant Tukadoji Maharaj, Shri Sant Gadge Maharaj, Warhadi Mandali | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Madhukar Keche''' ([[Devanagari]]: मधुकर केचे) (1932 - 1993) was a [[Marathi people|Marathi]] writer from [[Maharashtra]], [[India]].
His writings include: * Biographies ''Rashtrasant Tukadoji Maharaj'' (राष्ट्रसंत तुकडोजी महाराज) and ''Shri Sant Gadge Maharaj'' (श्रीसंत गाडगे महाराज) * A collection of biographical sketches ''Warhadi Mandali'' (वर्‍हाडी मंडळी) * Travelogue ''Majhi Kahi Gawe'' (माझी काही गावं) * Novel ''Moti Jyanchya Poti'' (मोती ज्यांच्या पोटी) * Collection of short stories ''Akhar Angan'' (आखर आंगण) * Travel travelling 'Gandhi Parisar' Musings in the Gandhi Ashram Sewagram. Very thought provoking and real.
A Phd thesis on his work is also published. He was resident of Amravati but traveled all over Maharashtra. He was also a well known poet.
{{DEFAULTSORT:Keche, Madhukar}} [[Category:Marathi-language writers]] [[Category:1932 births]] [[Category:1993 deaths]]
