{{notability|date=May 2015}}
'''PATR-II''' is a linguistic formalism used in [[computational linguistics]], developed by [[Stuart M. Shieber]]. It uses [[context-free grammar]] rules and [[feature structure|feature constraints]] on these rules.

==External links==
* [http://www.sil.org/pcpatr/manual/pcpatr.html#overview PC-PATR], an implementation of PATR-II for PC and Unix systems.

