{{Infobox language |name=Sanavirón |nativename= |states=[[Argentina]] |ethnicity = Sanavirones |extinct=? |familycolor=American |family=unclassified |iso3=none |glotto=none |linglist=1nf }}
'''Sanavirón''' is an extinct and unclassified language once spoken near [[Córdoba, Argentina]]. Loukotka (1968) classified it as a language isolate, but there is insufficient data to justify this (Campbell & Grondona 2012).
