{{Infobox settlement| settlement_type = | subdivision_type = Country | official_name = Zalizne| native_name = Залізне| subdivision_name = Ukraine| image_skyline = File:Дзержинск Артемово Памятник на братской могиле.jpg| image_caption = Soviet war monument in Zalizne| image_seal =| image_flag = | subdivision_type1 = Oblast| region_type_local = Raion| subdivision_name1 = [[Donetsk Oblast|Donetsk]]| population_total = 5598| population_as_of = 2013| area_total_km2 = | established_date = | established_title = Founded| established_title2 = |established_date2 = |elevation_m = | coordinates = {{coord|47|47|N|38|29|E|region:UA_type:city|display=inline,title}} | | website = }} '''Zalizne''' ({{lang-uk|Залізне}}, formerly '''Artemove''' ({{lang-uk|Артемове}}, {{lang-ru|Артёмово}}) is a city in [[Toretsk municipality]], [[Donetsk Oblast]] ([[oblast|province]]) of [[Ukraine]]. Population: {{Ua-pop-est2013|5,598}}; 6,725 (2001).
On 19 May 2016, Artemove was renamed Zalizne conform to the law prohibiting names of Communist origin.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.unn.com.ua/uk/news/1572273-rada-pereymenuvala-dniprodzerzhinsk-na-kamyanske-dopovneno|title=Рада перейменувала Дніпродзержинськ на Кам'янське|date=19 May 2016|publisher=Українські Національні Новини|language=Ukrainian|accessdate=19 May 2016}}</ref>
